    (13678, 'unadorned', 'TOEFL_2', '朴素的,未装饰的', 'adj', '''ʌnə''dɔ:nd', 'ʌnə''dɔːnd', 'They liked their churches to be unadorned.', '他们希望他们的教堂朴素无华。'),
    (13679, 'brave', 'TOEFL_2', '勇敢的', 'adj', 'brev', 'breɪv', 'brave soldiers', '勇敢的士兵'),
    (13680, 'compatible', 'TOEFL_2', '谐调的,兼容的', 'adj', 'kəm''pætəbl', 'kəm''pætɪb(ə)l', 'The new software is IBM compatible (= can be used with IBM computers ) .', '这个新软件与IBM的计算机兼容。'),
    (13681, 'inn', 'TOEFL_2', '(尤指乡村或公路边的) 旅馆', 'n', 'ɪn', 'ɪn', 'We’re staying at the Holiday Inn.', '我们住在假日酒店。'),
    (13682, 'multitude', 'TOEFL_2', '多数, 群众', 'n', 'ˈmʌltɪˌtud, -ˌtjud', '''mʌltɪtjuːd', 'I had never seen such a multitude of stars before.', '我以前从未见过这么多的星星。'),
    (13683, 'paraphrase', 'TOEFL_2', '解释', 'v', 'ˈpærəfreɪz', '''pærəfreɪz', 'To paraphrase Finkelstein, mathematics is a language, like English.', '芬克尔斯坦的意思是，数学是一门语言，就像英语一样。'),
    (13684, 'unselfish', 'TOEFL_2', '无私的,慷慨的', 'adj', 'ʌn''sɛlfɪʃ', 'ʌn''selfɪʃ', 'She started to get a reputation as an unselfish girl with a heart of gold.', '她开始得到有着金子般心灵的无私女孩的名声。'),
    (13685, 'disco', 'TOEFL_2', '迪斯科舞厅', 'n', '''dɪsko', '''dɪskəʊ', 'the school disco', '学校的迪斯科舞会'),
    (13686, 'ragtime', 'TOEFL_2', '拉格泰姆音乐', 'n', '''ræɡtaɪm', '''rægtaɪm', 'Joplin is considered the foremost composer of ragtime music.', '吉普林被认为是拉格泰姆（Ragtime）音乐最重要的作曲家。'),
    (13687, 'unrestricted', 'TOEFL_2', '自由的,无限制的', 'adj', ',ʌnrɪ''strɪktɪd', 'ʌnrɪ''strɪktɪd', 'Freedom to pursue extracurricular activities is totally unrestricted.', '参加课外活动的自由完全不受限制。'),
    (13688, 'quasar', 'TOEFL_2', '恒星状球体, 类星体', 'n', '''kwezɑr', '''kweɪzɑː; -sɑː', 'This quasar was the only one without a known host galaxy.', '这个类星体似乎无依无傍，不在任何一个星系当中。'),
    (13689, 'bedroom', 'TOEFL_2', '卧室', 'n', '''bɛdrum', '''bedruːm; -rʊm', 'a hotel with 50 bedrooms', '有50间客房的旅馆'),
    (13690, 'quill', 'TOEFL_2', '羽茎,大翎毛', 'n', 'kwɪl', 'kwɪl', 'She dipped a quill in ink, then began to write.', '她把羽毛笔蘸进墨水中，然后开始写字。'),
    (13691, 'bolster', 'TOEFL_2', '垫子', 'n', '''bolstɚ', '''bəʊlstə', 'I''ll bolster you up.', '我支持你。'),
    (13692, 'halt', 'TOEFL_2', '停止,暂停', 'n', 'hɔlt', 'hɔːlt', 'Heavy snowfalls brought traffic to a halt (= made it stop moving ).', '大雪使得交通陷于停顿。'),
    (13693, 'exhale', 'TOEFL_2', '呼气,发出', 'v', 'ɛks''hel', 'ɪks''heɪl; eks-', 'Take a deep breath, then exhale slowly.', '深吸一口气，然后慢慢呼出。'),
    (13694, 'angstrom', 'TOEFL_2', '[物理]埃(长度单位)', 'n', '''æŋstrəm', '''æŋstrəm', 'I like the angstrom. It is 10 to the minus 10 meters.', '我喜欢单位，埃，它等于10的负10次方米。'),
    (13695, 'microscopy', 'TOEFL_2', '显微镜检查,显微镜使用', 'n', 'maɪ''krɑskəpi', 'maɪ''krɒskəpɪ', 'Not only might it have applications in fields such as microscopy, but it apparently also has the ability to optically store data forever.', '它不仅可以在诸如显微镜之类的领域得到应用，显然它同时也具有实现永久性光存储的能力。'),
    (13696, 'narcotic', 'TOEFL_2', '麻醉药,镇静剂', 'n', 'nɑr''kɑtɪk', 'nɑː''kɒtɪk', 'The truth of Johnson’s comment was recently brought home to me by the serene calm of a resident who was treating a particularly complicated narcotic-dependent patient.', '最近，一位住院医生对待一位异常复杂的麻醉药依赖病人的平静态度让我领会到了塞缪尔.约翰逊这句话的真谛。'),
    (13697, 'complication', 'TOEFL_2', '复杂化, (使复杂的)因素', 'n', ',kɑmplɪ''keʃən', 'kɒmplɪ''keɪʃ(ə)n', 'The fact that the plane was late added a further complication to our journey.', '飞机误点给我们的旅行带来了更大的麻烦。'),
    (13698, 'rupture', 'TOEFL_2', '破裂,裂开', 'v', '''rʌptʃɚ', '''rʌptʃə', 'The pipe will rupture at its weakest point.', '管道最薄弱的地方会破裂的。'),
    (13699, 'abrasion', 'TOEFL_2', '磨损', 'n', 'ə''breʒən', 'ə''breɪʒ(ə)n', 'extra protection against abrasion', '防止磨损的额外保护'),
    (13700, 'proportionally', 'TOEFL_2', '成比例地,相称地', 'adv', 'prəu''pɔ:ʃənəli', 'prəu''pɔ:ʃənəli', 'However, because of on-chip space limitations, the TLB size can not be increased proportionally.', '然而，由于芯片空间的限制，TLB 的大小不能成比例地增加。'),
    (13701, 'freighter', 'TOEFL_2', '货船,承运人', 'n', '''fretɚ', '''freɪtə', 'The artificial reef, the Triangle, was put together from a freighter, a barge and -- this is the Palm Beach area, after all -- an old Rolls Royce.', '人工鱼礁、百慕大三角通过货船和驳船装运相连在一起，中间的区域便是棕榈滩。 这卡片终究堪比“一辆古老的劳斯莱斯”。'),
    (13702, 'morality', 'TOEFL_2', '道德,品行', 'n', 'məˈræləti', 'məˈræləti', '...standards of morality and justice in society.', '…社会中道德和正义的标准。'),
    (13703, 'yardstick', 'TOEFL_2', '<美> 码尺, 准绳', 'n', '''jɑrd''stɪk', '''jɑːdstɪk', 'The book gives a yardstick for measuring assets.', '该书为评估资产提供了一种标准。'),
    (13704, 'exalt', 'TOEFL_2', '晋升', 'v', 'ɪɡ''zɔlt', 'ɪg''zɔːlt; eg-', 'But it can also inspire and uplift and exalt, because power can be used to help people accomplish marvelous things.', '但是，权力也可以激励人、振奋人和提升人，因为它可以帮助人们成就非同寻常的事业。'),
    (13705, 'monoxide', 'TOEFL_2', '一氧化物', 'n', 'mɔ''nɔksaid, mə-', 'mə''nɒksaɪd', 'Then, if the mix of waste is correct, the carbon and oxygen atoms involved recombine to form carbon monoxide and the hydrogen atoms link up into diatomic hydrogen molecules.', '接下去，如果废物的组合是合适的，碳原子和氧原子会重新组合形成一氧化碳，而氢原子则结合起来形成双原子的氢分子。'),
    (13706, 'comply', 'TOEFL_2', '顺从,答应', 'v', 'kəm''plaɪ', 'kəm''plaɪ', 'The commander said that the army would comply with the ceasefire.', '指挥官说过部队会遵从停火协议。'),
    (13707, 'owe', 'TOEFL_2', '欠(债等),感激', 'v', 'o', 'əʊ', 'How much do I owe you (= often used to show that you want to pay for something )?', '我该付你多少钱？'),
    (13708, 'ingot', 'TOEFL_2', '[冶]锭铁, 工业纯铁', 'n', '''ɪŋgət', '''ɪŋgət', '...gold ingots.', '...金锭。'),
    (13709, 'premature', 'TOEFL_2', '未成熟的,早熟的', 'adj', ',primə''tʃʊr', '''premətjʊə', 'his premature death due to cancer', '他因癌症而早逝'),
    (13710, 'grievance', 'TOEFL_2', '委屈, 冤情, 不平', 'n', '''grivəns', '''griːv(ə)ns', 'anyone who has a legitimate grievance against the company', '凡是有正当理由对公司感到不满的人'),
    (13711, 'conjectural', 'TOEFL_2', '推测的,好推测的', 'adj', 'kən''dʒɛktʃərəl', 'kən''dʒektʃ(ə)r(ə)l', 'There is something undeniably conjectural about such claims.', '此类声明中绝对有推测的成分。'),
    (13712, 'knot', 'TOEFL_2', '(绳等的)结', 'n', 'nɑt', 'nɒt', 'One lace had broken and been tied in a knot.', '一根带子已经断了，被打成一个结。'),
    (13713, 'notch', 'TOEFL_2', '槽口,刻痕', 'n', 'nɑtʃ', 'nɒtʃ', 'Cut a notch near one end of the stick.', '在手杖的一端刻一个V形记号。'),
    (13714, 'photogrammetry', 'TOEFL_2', '照相测量法', 'n', ',fotə''ɡræmɪtri', ',fəʊtə(ʊ)''græmɪtrɪ', 'A survey of these surfaces was last undertaken in 1993 using photogrammetry — a technique that combines overlapping images — to achieve a somewhat limited resolution of 2cm.', '上一次对这些巨石的表面进行的测量工作是在1993年的时候，使用了摄影测量技术---通过这种技术可以把好多张照片合并起来---其极限分辨率可以达到2厘米。'),
    (13715, 'attire', 'TOEFL_2', '服装', 'n', 'ə''taiə', 'ə''taɪə', 'business attire', '商务着装，正装'),
    (13716, 'corrosion', 'TOEFL_2', '侵蚀,腐蚀状态', 'n', 'kə''roʒən', 'kə''rəʊʒ(ə)n', 'They are sprayed with oil to prevent corrosion.', '它们被喷了油以防腐蚀。'),
    (13717, 'upright', 'TOEFL_2', '正直的', 'adj', '''ʌpraɪt', '''ʌpraɪt', 'Katie was still awake, sitting bolt upright(= sitting with her back very straight ) staring at the television.', '凯蒂还醒着，坐得笔直，眼睛盯着电视。'),
    (13718, 'unravel', 'TOEFL_2', '拆开,拆开', 'v', 'ʌn''rævl', ',ʌn''rævəl', 'He could unravel a knot that others wouldn''t even attempt.', '他能解开其他人甚至不敢尝试的绳结。'),
    (13719, 'deft', 'TOEFL_2', '敏捷熟练的, 灵巧的', 'adj', 'deft', 'deft', 'He sketched her with quick, deft strokes.', '他给她画素描，下笔又快又熟练。'),
    (13720, 'robust', 'TOEFL_2', '精力充沛的', 'adj', 'ro''bʌst', 'rə(ʊ)''bʌst', 'The Secretary of State has made a robust defence of the agreement.', '国务卿对这项协议进行了强有力的辩护。'),
    (13721, 'sword', 'TOEFL_2', '剑', 'n', 'sɔːrd', 'sɔːd', 'The treaty hung like a sword of Damocles over French politics.', '这个条约好像一把达摩克利斯之剑悬在法国政坛之上。'),
    (13722, 'entomb', 'TOEFL_2', '埋葬, 成为的坟墓', 'v', 'ɪn''tum', 'ɪn''tuːm; en-', 'The city was entombed in volcanic lava.', '那个城市被火山熔岩掩埋了。'),
    (13723, 'burgher', 'TOEFL_2', '公民, 市民', 'n', '''bɝɡɚ', '''bɜːgə', 'Even take the word burgher or bourgeois.', '比如说"市民"或称之为"布尔乔亚"'),
    (13724, 'puffin', 'TOEFL_2', '[鸟]角嘴海雀', 'n', '''pʌfɪn', '''pʌfɪn', 'Despite 2010 starting and ending with much of the country swathed in snow, threatened species such as the puffin and the rare heath fritillary butterfly enjoyed successful breeding seasons.', '尽管2010年开始和结束时，英国的大部分地区都被大雪覆盖，对人们来说不算是好天气。 但英国的国民托管组织声称：在这一年里，英国的很多濒危物种，比如埃克斯莫尔的珍稀希斯豹纹蝶、坎布里亚郡的网纹毛毡衣蝶还有法内尔岛上的海雀，都很享受这适合繁殖的一年，数量大大增加。'),
    (13725, 'insoluble', 'TOEFL_2', '不能溶解的, 不能解决的', 'adj', 'ɪn''sɑljəbl', 'ɪn''sɒljʊb(ə)l', 'insoluble conflicts within the department', '部门内难以调和的冲突'),
    (13726, 'reliability', 'TOEFL_2', '可靠性', 'n', 'rɪ,laɪə''bɪləti', 'rɪ,laɪə''bɪlətɪ', 'I can assure you of the reliability of the information.', '我可以向你保证这消息是可靠的。'),
    (13727, 'unemployed', 'TOEFL_2', '失业的, 未被利用的', 'adj', ',ʌnɪm''plɔɪd', 'ʌnɪm''plɒɪd; -em-', 'an unemployed actor', '没戏演的演员'),
    (13728, 'preside', 'TOEFL_2', '主持,管理', 'v', 'prɪ''zaɪd', 'prɪ''zaɪd', 'I shall be pleased to preside at your meetings.', '我很高兴主持你们的会议。'),
    (13729, 'spacious', 'TOEFL_2', '广大的,大规模的', 'adj', '''speʃəs', '''speɪʃəs', 'a spacious living area', '宽敞的居住空间'),
    (13730, 'portraiture', 'TOEFL_2', '肖像画法', 'n', '''pɔrtrətʃɚ', '''pɔːtrɪtʃə', 'The dispute illuminates the primitive nature of our attitude to portraiture.', '这一争论阐释了我们对肖像画的态度的本性。'),
    (13731, 'talented', 'TOEFL_2', '有才能的', 'adj', '''tæləntɪd', '''tæləntɪd', 'a talented actor', '一名很有天赋的演员'),
    (13732, 'homework', 'TOEFL_2', '家庭作业, 副业', 'n', '''hom''wɝk', '''həʊmwɜːk', 'For homework, finish the exercise on page 14.', '家庭作业是完成第14页的练习。'),
    (13733, 'understate', 'TOEFL_2', '打着折扣说,有意轻描淡写', 'v', '''ʌndɚ''stet', 'ʌndə''steɪt', 'The press have tended to understate the extent of the problem.', '媒体想淡化问题的严重程度。'),
    (13734, 'narrate', 'TOEFL_2', '叙述,作解说', 'v', 'næret', 'nə''reɪt', 'a wildlife film narrated by David Attenborough', '一部由大卫•艾登堡解说的野生动物影片'),
    (13735, 'lean', 'TOEFL_2', '倾斜,倚靠', 'n', 'lin', 'liːn', 'trees leaning in the wind', '在风中东倒西歪的树木'),
    (13736, 'consort', 'TOEFL_2', '结交,符合', 'v', '''kɑn,sɔrt', '''kɒnsɔːt', 'The public has accepted Camilla, Prince Charles’s former mistress, as his consort.', '公众接受了作为前任情妇的卡米拉成为查尔斯王子的新配偶。'),
