    (15834, 'rarefy', 'TOEFL_2', '稀薄', 'v', '''rɛrə,fai', '''reərɪfaɪ', 'The insertion of an inner rod into the waveguide can rarefy the spectrum of the competing modes in the vicinity of the operating mode and restrict the mode competing effectively.', '在圆柱腔体内插入一个内导体将会使工作模式附近的模谱变稀，从而有效的抑制模式竞争。'),
    (15835, 'snipe', 'TOEFL_2', '[鸟]鹬', 'n', 'snaɪp', 'snaɪp', 'I propose that every time an American bags a snipe, the federal government should pay him or her $100.', '美国需要更多的猎鹬者，我提议一个美国人每捕到一只鹬，联邦政府支付给他100美元。'),
    (15836, 'intricately', 'TOEFL_2', '杂乱地,  复杂地', 'adv', 'ˈɪntrəkɪtlɪ', '''ɪntrɪkətlɪ', 'In areas where river deltas inject organic material and dissolved trace elements into the sea, for instance, it’s not clear how all of the intricately related processes will affect water chemistry.', '例如，在有些地区，河流三角洲将有机物质和溶解的微量元素注入海洋，目前还不清楚所有这些错综复杂的相关进程将如何影响水的化学性能。'),
    (15837, 'icon', 'TOEFL_2', '图标, 肖像', 'n', '''aɪkɑn', '''aɪkɒn; -k(ə)n', 'To open a new file, click on the icon.', '要打开新文档，点击该图标。'),
    (15838, 'antelope', 'TOEFL_2', '羚羊', 'n', '''æntɪlop', '''æntɪləʊp', 'The hunter disembowelled the antelope.', '猎人取出羚羊的内脏。'),
    (15839, 'interferometer', 'TOEFL_2', '干涉计', 'n', ',ɪntɚfɪ''rɑmətɚ', ',ɪntəfə''rɒmɪtə', 'One possibility, according to Hogan, would be to use a device called an atom interferometer.', '霍根说，一种可行方式是使用所谓的“原子干涉仪”设备。'),
    (15840, 'hardworking', 'TOEFL_2', '努力工作的,  勤奋的', 'adj', '''hɑrd,wɝkɪŋ', '''hɑːd,wɜːkɪŋ', 'He was hardworking and energetic.', '他很努力且精力充沛。'),
    (15841, 'proprietorship', 'TOEFL_2', '所有权', 'n', 'prə''praɪətɚ,ʃɪp', 'prə''praiətə,ʃip', 'She would preside over the innocent repasts of the young heir, with ineffable satisfaction, almost with an air of joint proprietorship with Richards in the entertainment.', '她会怀着难以形容的满意心情主持这位年轻继承人的天真的用餐，那副神态就几乎像在这个款待中她跟理查兹共同享有所有权似的。'),
    (15842, 'imbibe', 'TOEFL_2', '吸收', 'v', 'ɪm''baɪb', 'ɪm''baɪb', 'She had imbibed the traditions of her family.', '她受到了自己家庭传统的影响。'),
    (15843, 'agility', 'TOEFL_2', '敏捷, 活泼', 'n', 'ə''dʒiləti', 'ə''dʒɪlətɪ', 'If for some reason you don''t have or cannot adopt these values, then you should not worry about agility.', '如果因为某些原因您没有或者不能采用这些价值，那么您就不需要为敏捷而操心了。'),
