    (15870, 'polarity', 'TOEFL_2', '极性', 'n', 'pə''lærəti', 'pə(ʊ)''lærɪtɪ', 'Whether you want to call it magnetism, polarity,electricity, thought, intelligence or charisma, it''s still attraction, and it invests everything—animal, vegetable or mineral.', '不论你管它叫磁性、极性、活力、体贴、智慧还是魅力，它们都是吸引力，而且它适用于一切------动物、蔬菜或矿物。'),
    (15871, 'ferromagnetic', 'TOEFL_2', '铁磁的', 'adj', ',fɛromæɡ''nɛtɪk', ',ferə(ʊ)mæg''netɪk', 'When they gradually increased the repulsive forces between the atoms, they observed several features indicating that the gas had become ferromagnetic.', '他们利用红外线激光束捕获超冷锂原子气团，将其冷却到仅比绝对零度高亿分之十五开尔文。 当逐渐增加原子间斥力时，研究人员观察到的几个现象表明气体已经变得具有强磁性。'),
    (15872, 'afterward', 'TOEFL_2', '然后, 后来', 'adv', 'ˈæftərwərd', '''ɑːftəwəd', 'Shortly afterward, police arrested four suspects.', '之后不久，警方逮捕了４名嫌疑犯。'),
    (15873, 'occupant', 'TOEFL_2', '占有者, 居住者', 'n', '''ɑkəpənt', '''ɒkjʊp(ə)nt', 'The furniture had been left by the previous occupants.', '家具是先前的住户留下的。'),
    (15874, 'inflexible', 'TOEFL_2', '不可弯曲的, 僵硬的', 'adj', 'ɪn''flɛksəbl', 'ɪn''fleksɪb(ə)l', 'This approach is too inflexible and too costly.', '这个方法太死板，而且花费也太高。'),
    (15875, 'lotus', 'TOEFL_2', '[植] 莲(花)', 'n', '''lotəs', '''ləʊtəs', 'The soul unfolds itself, like a lotus of countless petals.', '灵魂伸展绽放，就像一朵有无数花瓣的莲花。'),
    (15876, 'inexplicable', 'TOEFL_2', '无法解释的，难理解的', 'adj', ',ɪnɪk''splɪkəbl', ',ɪnɪk''splɪkəb(ə)l; ,ɪnek-; ɪn''eksplɪ-', 'inexplicable behaviour', '费解的行为'),
    (15877, 'nineteen', 'TOEFL_2', '十九', 'num', ',naɪn''tin', 'naɪn''tiːn; ''naɪntiːn', 'It was nineteen minutes past seven.', '当时是7点19分。'),
    (15878, 'therapeutic', 'TOEFL_2', '治疗的, 治疗学的 n治疗剂, 治疗学家', 'adj', ',θɛrə''pjutɪk', ',θerə''pjuːtɪk', 'Some claim that the herb has therapeutic value for treating pain.', '有些人称这种草药具有止痛的疗效。'),
